Introduction

ALICE (formerly known as ELRIS) is a female duo under NS ENM. Originally as five, they debuted on June 1, 2017, with their first mini album "We, First".

On February 12, 2020, it was announced that 2 new members will be added to the lineup, EJ and Chaejeong, for their comeback with "Jackpot".

On December 1, 2021, they transferred from Hunus Entertainment to IOK Company. On April 11, 2022, the group's name was rebranded to ALICE, with Hyeseong now going by the stage name Yeonje and Bella (now going by the stage name Do-A).

On April 26, 2024, IOK Company announced that Sohee's exclusive contract will expire in May 2024 and she will be retiring from the industry.

On May 3, 2024, Do-A and Yukyung announced on social media that their exclusive contracts with IOK Company had expired, and they would be leaving the group. The same day, Karin and Yeonje also announced their departure.
